Escape velocity on earth, $v_{e}=\sqrt{\frac{2 G M_{e}}{R_{e}}}=11 \mathrm{~km} s^{-1}$
$\begin{array}{l}
\therefore \quad \frac{\left(v_{e}\right)_{p}}{\left(v_{e}\right)_{e}}=\frac{\sqrt{\frac{2 G M_{p}}{R_{p}}}}{\sqrt{\frac{2 G M_{e}}{\mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{e}}}}}=\sqrt{\frac{M_{p}}{M_{e}} \times \frac{\mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{e}}}{R_{p}}} \\
=\sqrt{\frac{10 M_{e}}{M_{e}} \times \frac{\mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{e}}}{\mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{e}} / 10}}=10 \\
\therefore\left(v_{e}\right)_{p}=10 \times\left(v_{e}\right)_{e}=10 \times 11=110 \mathrm{~km} / \mathrm{s}
\end{array}$

Variation of acceleration due to gravity, $g$ with distance $d$ ' from centre of the earth
If $d  < R, g=\frac{G m}{R^{2}}, d \quad$ l.e., $g \propto d$ (straight line)
$\begin{array}{l}
\text { If } d=R, g_{x}=\frac{G m}{R^{2}} \\
\text { If } d>R, g=\frac{G m}{d^{2}} \quad \text { i.e., } g \propto \frac{1}{d^{2}}
\end{array}$

